{{Use Canadian English|date=August 2014}} {{Infobox television |show_name = Art in Action |image = |show_name_2 = |caption = |genre = arts |creator = |developer = |writer = |director = |creative_director = |presenter = George Swinton |starring = |judges = |voices = |narrated = |theme_music_composer = |opentheme = |endtheme = |composer = |country = {{CAN}} |language = [[English language|English]] |channel = [[CBC Television]] |first_run = |first_aired = 7 October 1959 |last_aired = 1 October 1961 |num_seasons = 2 |num_episodes = |status = |list_episodes = |executive_producer = |producer = |editor = |location = [[CBWT-DT|Winnipeg]] |cinematography = |camera = |runtime = 30 minutes |company = |distributor = |picture_format = |audio_format = |preceded_by = |followed_by = |related = |website = |production_website = }}{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2014}} '''''Art in Action''''' was a [[Television in Canada|Canadian]] arts television series which aired on [[CBC Television]] from 1959 to 1961.
==Premise== [[University of Manitoba]] School of Art professor George Swinton hosted this series from Winnipeg.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=iHsyAAAAIBAJ&pg=4864%2C3995279 | title=TV Weekly | newspaper=Ottawa Citizen | page=4 | date=30 June 1961 | accessdate=5 August 2014 }}</ref> The first season described the history, techniques and materials involved in sculpting and painting. The second season focused on the history and techniques of landscape painting<ref name=CCF>{{cite web | url=http://www.broadcasting-history.ca/programming/television/programming_popup.php?id=940 | first=John | last=Corcelli | date=June 2005 | title=Art in Action | publisher=Canadian Communications Foundation | accessdate=5 August 2014 }}</ref>
==Scheduling== The half-hour series aired in the first season on Wednesdays at 5:00&nbsp;p.m. (Eastern) from 7 October 1959 to 11 May 1960. A second season aired on Sundays 10:30&nbsp;p.m. from 2 July to 1 October 1961.
